  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance d&#x2019;Urgence pour les d&#xE9;plac&#xE9;s suites aux r&#xE9;centes inondations dans les provinces de Bujumbura Mairie, Bujumbura, Rumonge et Makamba.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving shelter and essential household item assistance to vulnerable communities affected by flooding. This IOM project distributes emergency shelter and essential household item kits, supports camp management in IDP sites, organizes recreational activities in safe spaces for women and children, provides unconditional cash transfers to enable 1,400 households to meet their shelter needs, provides cash-for-work to 200 households. The project provides life-saving assistance to 28,740 people, including 8,061 women, 5,417 men, 15,262 children, and 226 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
